race.comment: CAP CAVOUR (1) couldn't have been more impressive here fresh, reeling in his rivals and sprinting away to win by 3.6L over 1100m. The rise in trip won't be an issue and he still has some improvement to come on his ratings profile. Can bring up back-to-back victories. SIMPLY ROYALTY (4) wasn't far away first-up over the 1100m journey here 21 days ago and stretches out to the 1200m trip for the first time today. Will need some luck from the wide draw, but she stuck on well fresh and is expected to be better for that run. Can get the job done now. BLITZEM BABE (8) hasn't won for a while but his run two back at Kalgoorlie suggested she wasn't far away. Just plain off a freshen last start as favourite, but the blinkers go back on now and sharp improvement is on the cards. PURE QUALITY (7) hasn't been far away in both runs this time in and can be in the finish once again. MAKE DE FORTUNE (11) is not out of this first-up.
